{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"code":"GKeyFile","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parses .ini-like config files."}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef"},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileProtocol","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"KeyFileRef","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GKeyFile"},{"type":"text","text":" lets you parse, edit or create files containing groups of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"key-value pairs, which we call ‘key files’ for lack of a better name.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Several freedesktop.org specifications use key files. For example, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/specifications.freedesktop.org\/desktop-entry-spec\/latest\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/specifications.freedesktop.org\/icon-theme-spec\/latest\/","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The syntax of key files is described in detail in the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"overridingTitle":"Desktop Entry Specification","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Desktop Entry Specification","type":"text"}],"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/specifications.freedesktop.org\/desktop-entry-spec\/latest\/"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"here is a quick summary: Key files consists of groups of key-value pairs, interspersed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with comments."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# this is just an example","# there can be comments before the first group","","[First Group]","","Name=Key File Example\\tthis value shows\\nescaping","","# localized strings are stored in multiple key-value pairs","Welcome=Hello","Welcome[de]=Hallo","Welcome[fr_FR]=Bonjour","Welcome[it]=Ciao","","[Another Group]","","Numbers=2;20;-200;0","","Booleans=true;false;true;true"],"syntax":"txt"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lines beginning with a "},{"code":"#","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and blank lines are considered comments."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Groups are started by a header line containing the group name enclosed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"["},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"]"},{"type":"text","text":", and ended implicitly by the start of the next group or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the end of the file. Each key-value pair must be contained in a group.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Key-value pairs generally have the form "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"key=value"},{"text":", with the exception","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of localized strings, which have the form "},{"code":"key[locale]=value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", with a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"locale identifier of the form "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lang_COUNTRY"},{"type":"text","text":"MODIFIER`` where "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"COUNTRY"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and `MODIFIER` are optional. As a special case, the locale `C` is associated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with the untranslated pair `key=value` (since GLib 2.84). Space before and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"after the `=` character is ignored. Newline, tab, carriage return and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"backslash characters in value are escaped as `\\n`, `\\t`, `\\r`, and `\\\\`,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"respectively. To preserve leading spaces in values, these can also be escaped","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as `\\s`."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Key files can store strings (possibly with localized variants), integers,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"booleans and lists of these. Lists are separated by a separator character,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"typically ","type":"text"},{"code":";","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":",","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". To use the list separator character in a value in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a list, it has to be escaped by prefixing it with a backslash."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This syntax is obviously inspired by the .ini files commonly met","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"on Windows, but there are some important differences:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":".ini files use the ","type":"text"},{"code":";","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" character to begin comments,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"key files use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#"},{"type":"text","text":" character."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Key files do not allow for ungrouped keys meaning only","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"comments can precede the first group."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Key files are always encoded in UTF-8.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Key and Group names are case-sensitive. For example, a group called","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[GROUP]"},{"type":"text","text":" is a different from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[group]"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":".ini files don’t have a strongly typed boolean entry type,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"they only have ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GetProfileInt()"},{"type":"text","text":". In key files, only"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":" (in lower case) are allowed."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that in contrast to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/specifications.freedesktop.org\/desktop-entry-spec\/latest\/","overridingTitle":"Desktop Entry Specification","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Desktop Entry Specification"}],"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"groups in key files may contain the same key multiple times; the last entry wins."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Key files may also contain multiple groups with the same name; they are merged","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"together. Another difference is that keys and group names in key files are not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"restricted to ASCII characters.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here is an example of loading a key file and reading a value:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"c","code":["`g_autoptr(GError)` error = NULL;","`g_autoptr(GKeyFile)` key_file = g_key_file_new ();","","if (!g_key_file_load_from_file (key_file, \"key-file.ini\", flags, &error))","  {","    if (!g_error_matches (error, G_FILE_ERROR, G_FILE_ERROR_NOENT))","      g_warning (\"Error loading key file: `s`\", error->message);","    return;","  }","","g_autofree gchar *val = g_key_file_get_string (key_file, \"Group Name\", \"SomeKey\", &error);","if (val == NULL &&","    !g_error_matches (error, G_KEY_FILE_ERROR, G_KEY_FILE_ERROR_KEY_NOT_FOUND))","  {","    g_warning (\"Error finding key in key file: `s`\", error->message);","    return;","  }","else if (val == NULL)","  {","    \/\/ Fall back to a default value.","    val = g_strdup (\"default-value\");","  }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Here is an example of creating and saving a key file:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["`g_autoptr(GKeyFile)` key_file = g_key_file_new ();","const gchar *val = …;","`g_autoptr(GError)` error = NULL;","","g_key_file_set_string (key_file, \"Group Name\", \"SomeKey\", val);","","\/\/ Save as a file.","if (!g_key_file_save_to_file (key_file, \"key-file.ini\", &error))","  {","    g_warning (\"Error saving key file: `s`\", error->message);","    return;","  }","","\/\/ Or store to a GBytes for use elsewhere.","gsize data_len;","g_autofree guint8 *data = (guint8 *) g_key_file_to_data (key_file, &data_len, &error);","if (data == NULL)","  {","    g_warning (\"Error saving key file: `s`\", error->message);","    return;","  }","`g_autoptr(GBytes)` bytes = g_bytes_new_take (g_steal_pointer (&data), data_len);"],"syntax":"c"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GKeyFile","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"code":"GKeyFile","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFile"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GKeyFile"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef\/init()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef\/init(_:)-5cs5o","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef\/init(_:)-766bl","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef\/init(_:)-776w8","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef\/init(_:)-7qdi8","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef\/init(_:)-935ll","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFileRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/KeyFi